HEADWORD: Chievance
<hw>Chiev"ance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>chevance</ets> property, equiv. To <ets>chevisance</ets>, fr.
<ets>chevir</ets> to accomplish. See <er>Chevisance</er>.]</ety> <def>An
unlawful bargain; traffic in which money is exported as discount.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
